  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen run `truffle init` on a directory that already exists `truffle` gives an error.\r\n\r\n```Something already exists at the destination. `truffle init` and `truffle unbox` must be executed in an empty folder. Stopping to prevent overwriting data.```\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n`yarn add truffle`\r\n`yarn truffle init`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle should have an option `--force`, to force the creation of the directory, because install `node` dependencies `globally` are simple so bad behavior.\r\n\r\nAnd if the directory is just created as \"empty\", why not let the user just `--force` and avoid some workaround to bypass that limitation.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTruffle just stop the creation of the directories expected from `init` command\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS 10.13.6\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 4.1.14\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 8.11.3\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  5.6.0\r\n* yarn version (`yarn -v`): 1.9.4\r\n",
